    "answer_id" : 4600845,
    "question_id" : 4597850,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The accepted answer is the correct one. </p>\n\n<p>OTOH, the way I previously solved this was to add the following to all projects:</p>\n\n<pre><code>test.onlyIf { ! Boolean.getBoolean('skip.tests') }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Run the build with <code>-Dskip.tests=true</code> and all test tasks will be skipped.</p>\n"
